#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "`rpm` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:42
msgid "The rpm command allows you to install a package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "rpm [-i][-U] package.rpm [-e] package\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:48
msgid "Example (for a package named 'package'):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "rpm -ivh package.rpm\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option            | Description                                  |\n"
"|-------------------|----------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-i package.rpm`  | Installs the package.                        |\n"
"| `-U package.rpm`  | Updates an already installed package.        |\n"
"| `-e package.rpm`  | Uninstalls the package.                      |\n"
"| `-h`              | Displays a progress bar.                     |\n"
"| `-v`              | Informs about the progress of the operation. |\n"
"| `--test`          | Tests the command without executing it.      |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:63
msgid ""
"The `rpm` command also allows you to query the system package database by "
"adding the `-q` option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:65
msgid ""
"It is possible to execute several types of queries to obtain different "
"information about the installed packages. The RPM database is located in the "
"directory `/var/lib/rpm`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:67
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:79
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:152
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:350
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:505
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:513
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "rpm -qa\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:73
msgid "This command queries all the packages installed on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "rpm -q [-a][-i][-l] package [-f] file\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rpm -qil package\n"
"rpm -qf /path/to/file\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option           | Description                                                                                    |\n"
"|------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-a`             | Lists all packages installed on the system.                                                    |\n"
"| `-i __package__` | Displays the package information.                                                              |\n"
"| `-l __package__` | Lists the files contained in the package.                                                      |\n"
"| `-f`             | Shows the name of the package containing the specified file.                                   |\n"
"| `--last`         | The list of packages is given by installation date (the last installed packages appear first). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:94
msgid "!!! Warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "    After the `-q` option, the package name must be exact. Metacharacters (wildcards) are not supported.\n"
msgstr ""

