#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "DNF: Dandified Yum"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "**DNF** (**Dandified Yum**) is a software package manager, successor of **YUM** (**Y**ellow dog **U**pdater **M**odified). It works with **RPM** packages grouped in a local or remote repository (a directory for storing packages). For the most common commands, its usage is identical to that of `yum`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:140
msgid ""
"The `dnf` command allows the management of packages by comparing those "
"installed on the system with those in the repositories defined on the "
"server. It also automatically installs dependencies, if they are also "
"present in the repositories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:142
msgid ""
"`dnf` is the manager used by many RedHat based distributions (RockyLinux, "
"Fedora, CentOS, ...). Its equivalent in the Debian world is **APT** "
"(**A**dvanced **P**ackaging **T**ool)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "`dnf` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:146
msgid ""
"The `dnf` command allows you to install a package by specifying only the "
"short name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf [install][remove][list all][search][info] package\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install tree\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:158
msgid "Only the short name of the package is required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option                     | Description                                                          |\n"
"|----------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `install`                  | Installs the package.                                                |\n"
"| `remove`                   | Uninstall the package.                                               |\n"
"| `list all`                 | Lists the packages already in the repository.                        |\n"
"| `search`                   | Search for a package in the repository.                              |\n"
"| `provides */command_name`  | Search for a command.                                                |\n"
"| `info`                     | Displays the package information.                                    |\n"
"| `autoremove`               | Removes all packages installed as dependencies but no longer needed. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:171
