#, no-wrap
msgid "The EPEL repository"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:731
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is EPEL and how is it used?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:734
#, no-wrap
msgid "**EPEL** (**E**xtra **P**ackages for **E**nterprise **L**inux) is an open-source and free community-based repository maintained by the [EPEL Fedora Special Interest Group](https://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/epel/) that provides a set of additional packages for RHEL (and CentOS, Rocky Linux, and others) from the Fedora sources.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:736
msgid ""
"It provides packages that are not included in the official RHEL "
"repositories. These are not included because they are not considered "
"necessary in an enterprise environment or deemed outside the scope of RHEL. "
"We must not forget that RHEL is an enterprise class distribution, and "
"desktop utilities or other specialized software may not be a priority for an "
"enterprise project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:737
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:740
msgid ""
"Installation of the necessary files can be easily done with the package "
"provided by default from Rocky Linux."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:742
msgid "If you are behind an internet proxy:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:743
#, no-wrap
msgid "export http_proxy=http://172.16.1.10:8080\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:748
msgid "Then:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:749
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf install epel-release\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:754
msgid ""
"Once installed you can check that the package has been installed correctly "
"with the command `dnf info`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:755
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"dnf info epel-release\n"
"Last metadata expiration check: 1:30:29 ago on Thu 24 Mar 2022 09:36:42 AM CET.\n"
"Installed Packages\n"
"Name         : epel-release\n"
"Version      : 8\n"
"Release      : 14.el8\n"
"Architecture : noarch\n"
"Size         : 32 k\n"
"Source       : epel-release-8-14.el8.src.rpm\n"
"Repository   : @System\n"
"From repo    : epel\n"
"Summary      : Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux repository configuration\n"
"URL          : http://download.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel\n"
"License      : GPLv2\n"
"Description  : This package contains the Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux\n"
"             : (EPEL) repository GPG key as well as configuration for yum.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:775
msgid ""
"The package, as you can see from the package description above, does not "
"contain executables, libraries, etc... but only the configuration files and "
"GPG keys for setting up the repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:777
msgid ""
"Another way to verify the correct installation is to query the rpm database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:778
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rpm -qa | grep epel\n"
"epel-release-8-14.el8.noarch\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:784
msgid ""
"Now you need to run an update to let `dnf` recognize the repository. You "
"will be asked to accept the GPG keys of the repositories. Clearly, you have "
"to answer YES in order to use them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:785
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf update\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:790
msgid ""
"Once the update is complete you can check that the repository has been "
"configured correctly with the `dnf repolist` command which should now list "
"the new repositories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:791
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"dnf repolist\n"
"repo id            repo name\n"
"...\n"
"epel               Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux 8 - aarch64\n"
"epel-modular       Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux Modular 8 - aarch64\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:801
msgid "The repository configuration files are located in `/etc/yum.repos.d/`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:802
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ll /etc/yum.repos.d/ | grep epel\n"
"-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 1485 Jan 31 17:19 epel-modular.repo\n"
"-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 1422 Jan 31 17:19 epel.repo\n"
"-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 1584 Jan 31 17:19 epel-testing-modular.repo\n"
"-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 1521 Jan 31 17:19 epel-testing.repo\n"
