"metalink=https://mirrors.fedoraproject.org/metalink?repo=epel-source-$releasever&arch=$basearch&infra=$infra&content=$contentdir\n"
"enabled=0\n"
"gpgkey=file:///etc/pki/rpm-gpg/RPM-GPG-KEY-EPEL-8\n"
"gpgcheck=1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:845
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using EPEL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:848
msgid ""
"At this point, once configured, we are ready to install the packages from "
"EPEL. To start, we can list the packages available in the repository with "
"the command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/13-softwares.md:849
#, no-wrap
msgid "dnf --disablerepo=\"*\" --enablerepo=\"epel\" list available\n"
